<section xml:id="sec-3-4-arguments-with-quant" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Arguments with Quantifiers</title>
<p>
    We have seen in <xref ref="sec-3-1-arguments"/> that 
    quantified statments can lead to interesting arguments. 
    For example
</p>
<tabular halign="center">
    <row>
      <cell>All <m>A</m> are <m>B</m> </cell>
    </row>
    <row  bottom="minor">
      <cell>All <m>B</m> are <m>C</m>  </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\therefore \text{ All }A\text{ are }C</m></cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>
  <p>
    For example "All longshoremen are in a union" and "All unions have dues" 
    thus we can conclude that "All longshorement pay dues".
  </p>
<p>
    Next we have a far from complete list: 
</p>
<sbsgroup widths="55% 25%" valign="middle">
    <sidebyside>
        <p>
            Argument:
        </p>
        <p>
            Name:
        </p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
        <p></p>
        <p></p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
        <p>
            <tabular halign="center">
                <row  bottom="minor">
                  <cell><m>\forall x\text{ }P(x)</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell><m>\therefore\text{ } P(c)\text{ where }c\in\mathcal{U}</m></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
        </p>
        <p>
           Universal Instantiation
        </p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
        <p></p>
        <p></p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
        <p>
            <tabular halign="center">
                <row  bottom="minor">
                  <cell><m>P(c)\text{ for an arbitrary }c\in\mathcal{U}</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell><m>\therefore\text{ } \forall x\text{ }P(x)</m></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
        </p>
        <p>
            Universal Generalization
        </p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
        <p></p>
        <p></p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
        <p>
            <tabular halign="center">
                <row  bottom="minor">
                  <cell><m>\exists x\text{ }P(x)</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell><m>\therefore\text{ } P(c) \text{ for some }c\in\mathcal{U}</m></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
        </p>
        <p>
            Existential Instantiation
        </p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
        <p></p>
        <p></p>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
        <p>
            <tabular halign="center">
                <row  bottom="minor">
                  <cell><m>P(c)\text{ for some }c\in\mathcal{U}</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell><m>\therefore\text{ } \exists x\text{ }P(x)\vee Q</m></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
        </p>
        <p>
            Existential Generalization
        </p>
    </sidebyside>
</sbsgroup>
<p>
    These will be instrumental to our proofs invovling quantifiers shortly!
</p>
</section>